======================================================================
PART 5: F(-1) vs CYCLE STRUCTURE
  F(-1) = H - 2o. What determines o (odd-fwd path count)?
  Can we express o in terms of cycle counts?
======================================================================

--- n = 4 ---
  o determined by (H, c3)? False
    (H=1, c3=0): o in [0, 1]
    (H=3, c3=1): o in [0, 1, 2, 3]
    (H=5, c3=2): o in [1, 2, 3, 4]

--- n = 5 ---
  o determined by (H, c3)? False
    (H=1, c3=0): o in [0, 1]
    (H=3, c3=1): o in [0, 1, 2, 3]
    (H=5, c3=2): o in [0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
    (H=9, c3=3): o in [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8]
    (H=11, c3=4): o in [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 10]
    (H=13, c3=4): o in [4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]
    (H=15, c3=4): o in [6, 8]
    (H=15, c3=5): o in [4, 6, 8, 10]

  o determined by (H, |writhe|)? False

